# Group Recipient Validation

Recipient Validation checks email addresses to ensure you are sending to valid recipients.

Recipient Validation is available early for SparkPost beta testers. [Sign-up to be a beta tester](https://www.sparkpost.com/sparkpost-beta-tester/) if you'd like to try it out.
This feature is not currently available to EU accounts, check back soon for availability.


## Single Address Validation [GET /v1/recipient-validation/single/{address}]

Validate an email address. An address will either be returned as valid or invalid.
Any invalid email address responses will also provide a reason why it is invalid.

+ Request

+ Parameters

    + address (required, string, `some@ddress.com`)

+ Response 200 - Valid (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "results": {
                    "valid": true
                }
            }

+ Response 200 - Invalid (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "results": {
                    "valid": false,
                    "reason": "Invalid Domain"
                }
            }
